## Normalizer rules

### Whitelist pattern

`PAGE_SECTION_ACF_LAYOUTS` in `normalize-page-sections.ts` is a `Record<AnySectionT["type"], true>` object used as a type-safe whitelist. Every section key **must** appear here or the section is silently dropped.

```ts
const PAGE_SECTION_ACF_LAYOUTS = {
  my_new_section: true,
  // ...all other keys
} as const satisfies Record<AnySectionT["type"], true>;
```

The `satisfies` constraint makes TypeScript error if a key is missing from `AnySectionT` or vice versa.

### Switch pattern

`mapKnownPageSectionLayout()` switches on `layout: AnySectionT["type"]` and ends with `default: assertNever(layout)`. Every new case must be added or the build fails.

### Base object

Every case spreads `base = { _key, id }`:
```ts
const id = newSectionId();
const _key = keyOf(i, row);  // ACF row key or "row-{i}"
const base = { _key, id };
// then: return { ...base, type: "my_section", ... }
```

### Field access pattern

```ts
case "my_section":
  return {
    ...base,
    type: "my_section",
    title: asString(row.title),
    body: asHtml(row.body),
    image: asImage(row.image),
    button: asLink(row.button),
    items: Array.isArray(row.items)
      ? (row.items as { text?: unknown; icon?: unknown }[]).map((r) => ({
          text: asString(r.item),
          icon: asImage(r.icon),
        }))
      : [],
  };
```

