## Registry import conventions (`section-registry.ts`)

**Static imports** (top of file) — used for older/above-the-fold sections:
```ts
import { HeroSection } from "@/components/sections/hero/HeroSection";
```

**Dynamic imports** (preferred for all new sections, `ssr: true`):
```ts
const MySectionLazy = dynamic(
  () => import("@/components/sections/my-section").then((mod) => ({ default: mod.MySection })),
  { ssr: true }
);
```

Registry entry (both patterns use `asSection` cast):
```ts
export const sectionRegistry = {
  my_section: asSection(MySectionLazy as (p: { section: never; lang: Locale }) => ReactNode),
  // ...
} satisfies SectionRegistryShape;
```

`SectionRegistryShape = Record<AnySectionT["type"], SectionComponent>` — TypeScript errors if any key is missing.

