## ACF JSON structure

### Import bundle
**Canonical file:** `acf-import-bundle.json` at the **repository root** (this is what agents and PRs should edit).

**Theme mirror:** `wordpress/wp-content/themes/omb-headless/acf-import-bundle.json` — kept identical to the root file. Run **`npm run acf:sync-bundle`** to copy root → theme without pushing; **`npm run acf:push`** runs that sync first, then POSTs the canonical JSON to `POST /omb-headless/v1/acf-sync`. The mirror exists so the WordPress tree always carries the same bundle as the repo.

`npm run validate:sections` fails if root and theme JSON differ (normalized), so CI catches drift early.

### Local JSON
`wordpress/wp-content/themes/omb-headless/acf-json/group_*.json` — one file per field group, used by ACF Local JSON sync. Regenerate with `npm run acf:extract-local-json`.

### Page builder group
All flexible layout sections live inside the `group_omb_page_builder` field group, under the `page_builder` flexible content field. When adding a new layout:
1. Add a new `layout` entry to the `layouts` **object** on `page_builder` in **`acf-import-bundle.json` at the repo root** (canonical). (`layouts` is keyed by `layout_omb_*`, not a JSON array.)
2. Set `"name": "my_new_section"` (must match `acf_fc_layout` everywhere).
3. Add all sub-fields with keys following `field_omb_my_new_section_*`.
4. Run **`npm run acf:sync-bundle`** (updates the theme mirror) and **`npm run acf:push`** to sync to WordPress (push runs sync automatically).

### `pricing_packages` — package repeater (`items`)

Each row maps to `PricingPackageItemT` in `normalize-page-sections.ts`. ACF **names** (REST keys) are still `price_line`, `note`, and `small_print` for backwards compatibility; labels in the bundle read **Pricing title**, **Secondary title**, and **Pricing paragraph (optional)**. The normalizer exposes them as `pricingTitle`, `secondaryTitle`, and `pricingParagraph`. Legacy `pricing_title` / `secondary_title` / `pricing_paragraph` keys are read first when present. The old **Solves** fields were removed from the import bundle.

