## enrich-sections.ts — async enrichment pass

Called after normalization in page/template server components. Pattern:

```ts
const enriched = await enrichSections(sections, {
  lang,
  globals,
  pageSlugPath,          // for blog/case-study archive paths
  blogArchive,           // ?page= / ?s= parsed from URL
  caseStudyArchive,
});
```

Enrichment is **selective by section type**: only `testimonials`, `latest_posts`, `blog_post_overview`, `case_study_overview`, `design_showcase_grid`, `form_embed`, `free_demo_form`, and `faq_contact_split` (when `useForm`) receive async data. All other sections pass through unchanged.

Do not add synchronous logic to enrich-sections — it is intentionally async-only.
